We shall define the Prominence Index (I) as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}
$$ I={X}_1+{X}_2+{X}_3+{X}_4+{X}_5+{X}_6 $$
\end{document}I=X1+X2+X3+X4+X5+X6where
X
1 = whether article appeared in the front page (3 if yes and 2 if no)
X
2 = whether article appeared in main section (3 if yes and 2 if no)
X
3 = location of article on page (3 if left, above fold; 2 if right, above fold; 1 if left, below fold; and 0 if right, below fold)
X
4 = size of headline in cm (3 if > 1.91; 2 if > 1.27 and ≤ 1.91; 1 if > 0.64 and ≤ 1.27; and 0 if ≤ 0.64)
X
5 = presence of image or graphic (3 if yes and 2 if no)
X
6 = length of column in cm (3 if > 91.4; 2 if > 34.8 and ≤ 91.4; and 1 if ≤ 34.8).
